<h1>Supported Operating Systems</h1>

The skonfig runtime itself can be expected to work with all targets fulfilling
these requirements:
<ul>
	<li>
		runs a POSIX-compatible operating system
		(skonfig works with pretty much anything resembling UNIX which was
		released in this millennium),</li>
	<li>
		runs an SSH server which allows root login (or you provide your
		own <code>remote_exec</code> command).
	</li>
</ul>

When it comes to type support things become a bit more differentiated.
Support in <i>base</i> can be summarised as follows:

