<p>
	<h3>Support tiers:</h3>

	<dl>
		<dt>1</dt>
		<dd>
			<i>Fully supported</i><br />
			Actively used by maintainers. You can expect these systems to work
			very well with skonfig and all features should work as expected.
		</dd>

		<dt>2</dt>
		<dd>
			<i>Mostly supported</i><br />
			Most (if not all) features should be implemented and skonfig can be
			expected to generally work well with these systems.
			However, these systems are not actively used by maintainers.
			Bugs may need more time to get fixed and some features may be
			unimplemented.

			<p>Patches/pull requests are welcome.</p>
		</dd>

		<dt>3</dt>
		<dd>
			<i>Community support.</i><br />
			These are fun projects. There is no regular testing of these systems
			and features may be unimplemented or not working.
			Maintenance depends on community members sending patches.

			<p>Patches/pull requests are welcome.</p>
		</dd>
	</dl>
</p>
